column5: BRRRRRR!!!!! She's frosty here now. Just yesterday it was a balmy -11.

Winter has arrived here too Dave. It was -22C here last night just south of North Bay. It warmed up a little today.The lakes are froze over, not sure about the main body of Nipissing though.O ya, we also have over a foot of snow to go with it.
A Cessna Caravan made an emergency landing on Great Slave Lake yesterday. I can take the sled out now seems like there is good ice.
Thanx for the info.  Here in Niagara it's going up to +10 over the weekend.  Unfortunately for me -  I'm leaving for Fort McMurray Alberta in 4 hours where it is a balmy -15 & -16!
